title: For Sale:  LARUE PREDATAR
postcontent:
Brand new, in the box with all the swag (down to the Dillo Dust for your weekend barbecue), LaRue Tactical PredatAR 5.56 w/ 16 in barrel. Geissele trigger, FDE Magpul furniture, PredatAR Owner's Hat, LaRue's iconic stickers, pocket Constitutions, and FDE hard case. This rifle is a shooter, with its 3 shot group target from the factory measuring .346 MOA. Firm price, cash only deals, please.

XTRAXN™ is a proprietary chamber feature added to reduce frictional forces caused by pressure-expanded cartridge cases bearing against chamber walls. Facilitates reliable extraction through a wide range of temperature / chamber pressure extremes. XTRAXN™ extends extractor life, while having no effect on the firearm's accuracy. All this, and it dovetails well with the OBR's world-famous accuracy.

Specs: 
Caliber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO
Rifle Weight: 6.25 lb. (based on 16.1” barrel version, unloaded without optics)
Barrel Length: 16.1“
Barrel Material: Stainless Steel, Blackened.
Rifling Twist Rate: 1/8
Muzzle Thread Configuration: ½ x 28 *
Gas System: Mid-Length Direct Impingement
Trigger Group: Two-Stage Geissele
Rate of Fire: Semi automatic
Magazine Capacity: 30 rounds

PredatAR® 5.56 Overview:

The PredatAR® 5.56 is designed for those who are searching for a lightweight, ultra-reliable and accurate 5.56 mm NATO rifle for home-defense, competition-shooting or hunting. The PredatAR® takes the highly accurate OBR 5.56 “Lite” design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. By contouring the barrel, skeletonizing the handguard, lowering and simplifying the upper rail, and using a low-profile gas block, we were able to reduce roughly 2 pounds from the standard OBR 5.56 rifle.

The barrels are Stainless Steel, lightweight-profiled, Wylde chambered and feature polygonal rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in ½ x 28, with an A2 flash hider attached* (other muzzle devices can be added at an additional cost).

The handguards on the PredatAR® extend out 14.75”, to suit a larger range of shooting styles. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet 7075-T6, for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though we lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy. Each rifle ships with one, 3” long, MIL-STD-1913 detachable rail section.

Both models come with a 6-position Magpul MOE Stock and LaRue medium A-PEG™ Grip. The Bolt Carriers are hand-polished hard-chrome with max-staked carrier keys, with Texas-Spec Bolt assemblies. The lower assembly has the proven Geissele Two-Stage trigger.

(Iron Sights, Optics and QD mounts not included in price)

The XD-S disassembles just like the XD, however, with the XD-S, the disassembly lever cannot be manipulated with a magazine in the pistol. title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes $75
postcontent:
The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 4 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 62-A Pump .22 1937
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
I am now selling my all time favorite .22 rifle. I am going to regret this one for sure. 

 This little Winchester 62-A was made in 1937 according to the data base I looked in. It's a C&R obviously. The action extremely smooth is like all of these, and it's the sweetest carrying and shooting .22 I have ever owned. When I got it, my first shot with it was at an old Coke can at 100 yards, and I hit it smack in the middle. It's frankly just hard to miss with it, If I still lived back east and could squirrel hunt, there is no was I'd sell it. But where I live now, the squirrels are few and far between, and I haven't shot it in a year. I'm no longer collecting Winchesters, and other than a beat up old '94 this is the last one I have. There is a reason for it being the last one to go, lol.

 Metal is a very smooth brown/blue patina, with no pitting or damage that I can see. It's a really attractive rifle and looks better than my cell phone photos show. The bore is great, and like I said, it is accurate. much more accurate than it has a right to be.
 I think the finish on the forearm is original, and very nice. 

These shoot .22 S, L, and LR interchangeably. Lol, when shooting Shorts in it, you don't even need ear protection. Sounds like an air rifle! It has digested every type of ammunition I have ever put through it without a hiccup, and is a truly fine rifle. One of John Browning's best designs in my opinion.

 Contact me through Armslist with your phone number and we can arrange for you to see it here in Santa Fe. If you are too far away to come in person, I can ship to an FFL or a C&R. If you live in NM, I can ship to you without an FFL. You would just need to send me your NM Drivers License. 

Oh, and I can take a discreet online payment if you would rather use a credit card.
